				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Anyone ever try to pull these things?  
<br />

<br />
I see posts on necro/druid boards saying how good the exp is for them for lvl 40+.  I'm able to pull them (4 or 5) using my 42 enc and killing using a combo of AE mezes nukes and charm.  
<br />

<br />
The ones in Oasis no longer cast (not sure why) and move rather slow.  Using a sow potion, i'm wondering if Rain of Lava could be used to nuke them down.  3 waves at 172 each, compared to druids using ligntning strike which is around 180.  Their one nuke at 180 costs around 150 mana, compared to my 3 waves at 172 each for around 255 mana.  My pet will be ready and should be rather effective if the Spectres are running at 50% health.
<br />

<br />
Should be fun to try, I'll posts my results.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Just did it with my 43 mage.  Used earth pet first, full buffs.  I had kei, sow potions, lev rings
<br />

<br />
-Pulled one using Blaze (this take off 1 bub of health) 5 came at me!!  Luckily they move very slow and the ones in Oasis do not cast.
<br />

<br />
-Hit it again with Blaze as it reached the shore.(for some reason they did not take damage while moving in the water!!??)
<br />

<br />
-Ran around til they were all bunched up
<br />

<br />
-Sent in pet, all aggroed on it, then I cast Rain of Lava
<br />

<br />
-Pet died quickly, but by this time one Spectre was almost dead, others lost at least 1 bub of health
<br />

<br />
-I then ran around and nuked the first Spectre to death.
<br />

<br />
-I chose a new target and cast Blaze. (4 left now)
<br />

<br />
-I then cast a Fire pet then waited for the DS
<br />

<br />
-Sent pet in and nuked the target with Blaze again
<br />

<br />
-Pet died quickly, but the DS starts to take it's toll
<br />

<br />
-Ran around some more, nuked using Blaze, then summoned another fire pet
<br />

<br />
-Waited for DS, then sent it in.  At this time it was able to kill the other Spectre, while the other 3 chased me around
<br />

<br />
-Basically keep repeating these steps.  10-15 minutes later, 5 dead Specs nice loot and exp.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Once you break the spawn, 1 maybe 2 will pop.  2 were fairly easy, 1 doesn't stand a chance against your pet and nukes.  
<br />

<br />
Not as easy as I hoped, but after the spawn is broken, it's very easy.  Exp was better than DS for me and gnome guards.  Money was around 3pp max, with weapons dropped(some sell for 12pp at vendors) and gems around 10pp for the one I got.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
